<br>
&quot;Good evening sir, may we have a few moments to tell you about super_shit_scam_8714231?It'savailabeinyourareanowandwe....&quot;<br>
<br>
Say &quot;uh huh&quot; a few times and then wait for the right moment.  Trust me, wasting 90-120 seconds is worth it.  When you think you've heard enough, break in and tell them &quot;Wow, that sounds great!  Can you hold on for just a sec?&quot;<br>
<br>
Put the phone down.  I usually take the this time to do laundry, go to the store, tidy up, etc.  Check back every so often until they hang up.<br>
<br>
Now I realize this is difficult if YOU need to use the phone, or you have others living with you, but personally for me, it works great.  Why do this?  It's been purposed that if a large porportion of us did this on a regular basis, we could drive up average call times to the point where it would be no longer be profitable to call people.  Think about it, and give it a try if you can. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=673738">Gariet</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, HalfBreed Assassin<br>
